{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"privy-eloquent-nauplius","description":"## Why\nOne rebar store can be claimed from Claude Code AND OpenCode AND Codex AND Cursor. A bare\nsession id collides across tools, so it must be qualified by which harness produced it.\nThis story makes the feature genuinely multi-harness.\n\n## What\n- Extend the resolver's ordered native-var list with the confirmed OSS vars:\n  `OPENCODE_SESSION_ID` (shipped) and `CODEX_THREAD_ID` (convention), in popularity order\n  after `CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID`.\n- Record a harness provenance tag `data[\"harness\"]` (derived from `AI_AGENT`, e.g.\n  `claude-code_<ver>` / `opencode` / `codex` / `cursor`) folded to `state[\"claim_harness\"]`.\n- Optionally capture the secondary `CLAUDE_CODE_REMOTE_SESSION_ID` as\n  `data[\"remote_session\"]` -> `state[\"claim_remote_session\"]`.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: resolver list extension, harness tag + remote-session capture/fold, read rendering,\n  tests, docs of the cross-harness contract.\n- OUT: the per-harness capture SHIMS (S6) — this story is the store/record side.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Resolver recognizes `OPENCODE_SESSION_ID` and `CODEX_THREAD_ID` in the ordered list.\n- [ ] Claims record a `claim_harness` provenance tag distinguishing the source tool.\n- [ ] `CLAUDE_CODE_REMOTE_SESSION_ID` captured as a secondary field when present.\n- [ ] Read surface + docs updated; tests for each harness var and the harness tag.\n\n## Depends on\n- S2 (the record path exists).\n","id":"c557-8f46-0c16-4bf5","parent_id":"38ec-5f12-fdf5-4340","priority":3,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Multi-harness session capture: extend resolver var-list + record harness provenance tag"},"env_id":"724d9d0c-bc4c-4cc4-b96b-1a19356102e2","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783481184704180053,"uuid":"d019edc4-c6bd-4516-a3d9-d0d32ec275fd"}